The paper deals with video-based person Re-Identification (ReID) methods, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The use of wearable cameras and recording devices such as cellphones also involves multimedia (cs.MM) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The proposed framework also employs sensor meta data, which involves information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG).
